{"title":"Canyon adds Aeroad’s Pace bar and Torx 25 bolts to Ultimate and Endurace","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/canyon-ultimate-endurace-pace-bar","date":1747299600000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/canyon-ultimate-endurace-pace-bar\">Canyon adds Aeroad’s Pace bar and Torx 25 bolts to Ultimate and Endurace</a></p>\n\n<p>Canyon has upgraded the cockpit on its Ultimate and Endurace and made further changes to the Ultimate to improve ease of maintenance and tuning when out riding. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>New features include adopting the Pace modular cockpit, switching to almost universal Torx T25 bolts, a change to the Ultimate’s saddle clamp and new colour schemes.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>More cockpit options</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/589988-2025_ACT_Endurace_x_Action-shoot-Bregenz-Handlebar_4278_ALL-9b16dd-original-1747132754-970x648.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/589988-2025_ACT_Endurace_x_Action-shoot-Bregenz-Handlebar_4278_ALL-9b16dd-original-1747132754-970x648.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/589988-2025_ACT_Endurace_x_Action-shoot-Bregenz-Handlebar_4278_ALL-9b16dd-original-1747132754-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/589988-2025_ACT_Endurace_x_Action-shoot-Bregenz-Handlebar_4278_ALL-9b16dd-original-1747132754-768x513.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/589988-2025_ACT_Endurace_x_Action-shoot-Bregenz-Handlebar_4278_ALL-9b16dd-original-1747132754-1536x1026.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/589988-2025_ACT_Endurace_x_Action-shoot-Bregenz-Handlebar_4278_ALL-9b16dd-original-1747132754-2048x1368.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/589988-2025_ACT_Endurace_x_Action-shoot-Bregenz-Handlebar_4278_ALL-9b16dd-original-1747132754-750x501.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/589988-2025_ACT_Endurace_x_Action-shoot-Bregenz-Handlebar_4278_ALL-9b16dd-original-1747132754-1140x762.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/589988-2025_ACT_Endurace_x_Action-shoot-Bregenz-Handlebar_4278_ALL-9b16dd-original-1747132754-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/589988-2025_ACT_Endurace_x_Action-shoot-Bregenz-Handlebar_4278_ALL-9b16dd-original-1747132754-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/589988-2025_ACT_Endurace_x_Action-shoot-Bregenz-Handlebar_4278_ALL-9b16dd-original-1747132754-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption>Canyon</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Pace cockpit (Pace stands for Performance Adaptive Cockpit Ecosystem – so yes calling it a Pace cockpit is like saying ATM machine or Pin number), previously exclusive to the Canyon Aeroad, has now been carried over to the Ultimate and Endurace. According to Canyon, it ‘is designed to unlock performance options for riders and bring in a broader fit range through innovative cockpit modularity’.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Pace bar allows 50mm of width adjustment, so you can set your cockpit up as narrow or as wide as you want. It also offers 20mm of height adjustment, 5mm more than the width-adjustable CP0018 cockpit previously fitted to higher specs of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/canyon-endurace-review\">Endurace </a>and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/canyon-ultimate-review\">Ultimate</a>. The Pace bar will come as standard on all CFR and CF SLX specs of both bikes, as well as on all Ultimate CF SL specs barring the entry-level Ultimate CF SL 7. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As with the Aeroad, you can swap out the standard Classic Drops for Canyon’s Aero Drops, which have the flared design that’s now common on many of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-road-bike\">best road bikes</a>. This places the arms closer together when riding on the hoods, reducing the rider’s frontal area and thus improving aerodynamics, while keeping the drops wider for more control on descents.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Aero Drops also have a 105mm drop rather than the 130mm of the standard Classic Drops, which Canyon says allows riders to make more use of the drops, again potentially reducing frontal area. The reach is 10mm longer too, again helping riders to get more aero.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Pace bars also incorporate the Gear Groove, which was originally launched with the second generation <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/canyon-grail-cf-slx-8-di2-review\">Canyon Grail</a> gravel bike. This allows you to add aero bar extensions, a computer mount and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+6\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-6-970x300.webp\" alt=\"Cyclist banner saying 'escape to your favourite place every month', click here to subscribe'\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-6-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-6-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-6-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-6-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-6-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-6-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-6-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/11/ZFM_0084-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/11/ZFM_0084-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/11/ZFM_0084-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/11/ZFM_0084-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/11/ZFM_0084-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/11/ZFM_0084-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/11/ZFM_0084-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/11/ZFM_0084-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/11/ZFM_0084-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/11/ZFM_0084-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/11/ZFM_0084-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The modular design also makes packing a bike for travel easier, as there are just four Torx bolts to undo to loosen the drops from the central T-bar and no need to remove or rotate the stem.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When Cyclist’s Laurence Kilpatrick swapped to the Aero Drops from the Classic Drops during his review of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/canyon-aeroad-cfr-review-2024\">Canyon Aeroad CFR</a>, he noted that ‘switching over to the Aero Drops changed the ride experience on straight-line flats and white-knuckle descents notably. Even a few degrees of kink in the drops can have a big effect on a rider’s weight distribution and balance, especially when cornering at speed. It was a confidence-inspiring change.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The bad news is that the Aero Drops are a £219.95 / $229.95 add-on purchase, rather than being an option when selecting your bike, with even the Aeroad coming as standard with the Classic Drops. The Aero Extensions cost an additional £479.95 and aren’t yet available in the US.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/canyon-aeroad-cfr-review-2024\">Canyon Aeroad CFR 2024 road bike review</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/canyon-aeroad-ultimate-endurace-compared\">Canyon Aeroad vs Ultimate vs Endurace: The best Canyon road bike in 2025</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-endurance-road-bikes\">Best endurance road bikes 2025 reviewed for comfort on long rides</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-road-bike\">Best road bikes 2025 reviewed and rated</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-aero-bikes\">Best aero road bikes 2025: Ride faster for less effort</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Plus easier maintenance</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/590012-2026_TOP-6_ultimate_cfr-axs_4071_R102_P09_tx25_as_jpg-ea1c56-original-1747134273-970x970.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/590012-2026_TOP-6_ultimate_cfr-axs_4071_R102_P09_tx25_as_jpg-ea1c56-original-1747134273-970x970.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/590012-2026_TOP-6_ultimate_cfr-axs_4071_R102_P09_tx25_as_jpg-ea1c56-original-1747134273-300x300.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/590012-2026_TOP-6_ultimate_cfr-axs_4071_R102_P09_tx25_as_jpg-ea1c56-original-1747134273-150x150.webp 150w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/590012-2026_TOP-6_ultimate_cfr-axs_4071_R102_P09_tx25_as_jpg-ea1c56-original-1747134273-768x768.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/590012-2026_TOP-6_ultimate_cfr-axs_4071_R102_P09_tx25_as_jpg-ea1c56-original-1747134273-1536x1536.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/590012-2026_TOP-6_ultimate_cfr-axs_4071_R102_P09_tx25_as_jpg-ea1c56-original-1747134273-2048x2048.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/590012-2026_TOP-6_ultimate_cfr-axs_4071_R102_P09_tx25_as_jpg-ea1c56-original-1747134273-75x75.webp 75w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/590012-2026_TOP-6_ultimate_cfr-axs_4071_R102_P09_tx25_as_jpg-ea1c56-original-1747134273-350x350.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/590012-2026_TOP-6_ultimate_cfr-axs_4071_R102_P09_tx25_as_jpg-ea1c56-original-1747134273-750x750.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/590012-2026_TOP-6_ultimate_cfr-axs_4071_R102_P09_tx25_as_jpg-ea1c56-original-1747134273-1140x1140.webp 1140w\" /><figcaption>Canyon</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>There’s also an update to the Ultimate’s bolts, so that almost all use a Torx 25 head. The bikes’ thru-axle has a T25 head and its lever is removable so that you can set it to work on any other bolts that need adjusting when you’re out riding. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Canyon has also updated the Ultimate’s saddle clamp, making it easier to adjust saddle position and tilt, and there have been slight updates to the paint schemes for the Ultimate and Endurace too.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/canyon-ultimate-endurace-pace-bar\">Canyon adds Aeroad’s Pace bar and Torx 25 bolts to Ultimate and Endurace</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Pnorman","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"5931f67b816d0174cf405c146af186aa8ed2a94eb08b8d79d1107d98a67d80b1","category":"Cycling"}